The paper deals with multi-user multi-input multi-output transmissions for millimeter-wave systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a new precoding structure for combating multi-user interference, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of hybrid precoding architecture is also mentioned, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of feedback for channel reconstruction, which is a topic related to computer communications (cs.COM).
